The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Wednesday, June 18, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Wednesday, June 18, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Lower Circular Road, between Camac Street and Lansdowne Road, as the final phase of work on the AJC Bose Road flyover will be taken up. Buses and minibuses heading from Beckbagan to Alipore zoo will take the Lansdowne Road-Elgin Road-Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Chowringhee-Queensway-Hospital Road-Lower Circular Road route. Those travelling east towards Beckbagan will take the Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Hazra Road-Ballygunge Phari-Syed Amir Ali Avenue route. 				 																Book				 																																	June Maliah, Konkona Sen Sharma and others will read excerpts from Anjana Basus novel, Curses in the Ivory, at Sasha, Mirza Ghalib Street, 6 pm.				 																Dance				 																																	Link the Arts, a dance presentation by Sapphire Creations, at American Center at 7 pm.				 																Seminar				 																																	A national-level seminar on pantomime, organised by Indian Mime Theatre, at State Youth Centre, 10 am.				 																Meditation				 																																	A workshop on meditation, organised by Chinmaya Mission, at GD Birla Sabhagar, 7 pm to 8.30 pm.				 																Theatre				 																																	A theatre workshop for children at Aikatan, Salt Lake, from 10 am to 5 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	Prints and posters of European and Indian masters at Vikalp, Swabhumi.
